---

## 5. Exact Deployment Steps — in order
```
Step 1 — Supabase
  → supabase.com → New project → Settings → Database → copy connection string
  → Replace "postgres://" with "postgresql://" in the URL

Step 2 — Upstash Redis
  → upstash.com → Create database → Copy "REDIS_URL" (starts with rediss://)

Step 3 — AWS S3
  → Create bucket "streamsync-videos" → region ap-south-1
  → Permissions → Block public access → OFF
  → Add bucket policy (public read):
    {
      "Version": "2012-10-17",
      "Statement": [{
        "Effect": "Allow",
        "Principal": "*",
        "Action": "s3:GetObject",
        "Resource": "arn:aws:s3:::streamsync-videos/*"
      }]
    }
  → Upload your 4-5 MP4 files manually
  → Copy each URL: https://streamsync-videos.s3.ap-south-1.amazonaws.com/video1.mp4
  

Step 4 — Render
  → render.com → New Web Service → connect GitHub repo
  → Root directory: backend
  → Add env vars: DATABASE_URL, REDIS_URL, S3_BASE_URL
  → Deploy → copy your .onrender.com URL

Step 5 — Vercel
  → vercel.com → Import GitHub repo
  → Root directory: frontend
  → Add env var: VITE_API_URL = your Render URL
  → Deploy

Step 6 — Point kapilraghav.info/streamsync
  → In your portfolio repo, add a redirect or iframe
  → Or in Vercel, add kapilraghav.info as custom domain